==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Decumbent
<hw>De*cum"bent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>decumbens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>decumbere</ets>;
<ets>de-</ets> + <ets>cumbere</ets> (only in comp.), <ets>cubare</ets>
to lie down.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Lying down; prostrate;
recumbent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>decumbent</qex> portraiture of a woman.</q>
<rj><qau>Ashmole.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Reclining on the ground, as if too
weak to stand, and tending to rise at the summit or apex; <as>as, a
<ex>decumbent</ex> stem</as>.</def> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decumbently</ent>⟦br⟧
